post_text: PPS Family & Community Engagement would like to thank all of our PTO Leaders who took the time out of their busy schedule to attend today's training. Your continuous efforts to help us bridge the gap between the classroom and the real world challenges our students face is one that is greatly appreciated .We all have a responsibility to create a community our children deserve. Thank you All for stepping up and being a part of the solution . So far this school year 30 different PPS PTOs have been trained. This could not happen without the support of our FCE team of volunteers, Ms. Peron, Ms. Shafer, BOE Commissioners, President Robert Scott , the entire PTO Leadership Executive team and many others. Special thank you to our trainers President Jonnine DeLoatch and her team of women from the Paterson Alumni Chapter Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc..

Your continuous efforts to help us bridge the gap between the classroom and the real world challenges our students face is one that is greatly appreciated .We all have a responsibility to create a community our children deserve. Thank you All for stepping up and being a part of the solution . So far this school year 30 different PPS PTOs have been trained. This could not happen without the support of our FCE team of volunteers, Ms. Peron, Ms. Shafer, BOE Commissioners, President Robert Scott , the entire PTO Leadership Executive team and many others. Special thank you to our trainers President Jonnine DeLoatch and her team of women from the Paterson Alumni Chapter Delta Sigma Theta Sorority, Inc..
